# Supabase migrations

## Migration file names

New migration files under **`supabase/migrations/`** must use Supabase’s **`YYYYMMDDHHmmss_description.sql`** prefix: **14 digits** for the timestamp, then an underscore and a short snake_case description.

- Include the **full time** — **`HH`**, **`mm`**, and **`ss`** (e.g. `20260507130542`), in **UTC**.
- **Do not** zero out minutes and seconds (or use a coarse synthetic time like `…120000`) when naming a **new** migration. Use the real time from **`supabase migration new`** or the current clock so same-day migrations sort and merge predictably.

Older migrations in the project may use round timestamps; leave them as-is unless you are renaming for a deliberate reason.

